---
// Mock of the real parent email Siko sends after every session.
// Structure mirrors main.js formatReportEmail() — eyebrow, name + subject,
// metadata, tone-colored headline border, activity line, focus bar,
// engagement bullets, concepts, "where stuck" cards with yellow border,
// strengths, recommended next, and the brand-statement footer.
//
// This particular scene shows a MULTI-SUBJECT session (Math + History)
// — the real product auto-detects subjects from screen content and the
// email subject line aggregates whatever was seen, so a kid switching
// from algebra homework to a history short-answer prompt produces one
// session report covering both. Demonstrates the range without claiming
// anything the product doesn't actually do.
---

<div class="email-frame">
  <div class="window-chrome">
    <div class="lights">
      <span class="light red"></span>
      <span class="light yellow"></span>
      <span class="light green"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="addr">
      <span class="from">From&nbsp;</span>Siko &lt;reports@trysiko.com&gt;
      <span class="sep">·</span>
      <span class="from">To&nbsp;</span>sarah@gmail.com, sarah-mom@gmail.com
    </div>
    <div class="spacer"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="subject-line">
    <span class="subject-eyebrow">Subject</span>
    Sarah &mdash; Math + History &mdash; Wed Apr 30 at 7:14 PM &mdash; 42 min
  </div>

  <div class="email-body">
    <div class="header">
      <div class="eyebrow">Siko &middot; Study session report</div>
      <div class="title">Sarah &middot; Math + History</div>
      <div class="meta">Wed, Apr 30 at 7:14 PM &middot; 42 min</div>
    </div>

    <div class="headline">
      Sarah worked through three linear-equation problems and a short-answer history prompt; got stuck distributing a negative term, and on naming the second cause of the American Revolution.
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Activity</div>
      <div class="activity-line">42 min total &middot; 33 min active, 9 min idle &middot; 5 hints &middot; 1 stuck moment</div>
      <div class="bar">
        <div class="bar-fill" style="width: 78%;"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="bar-caption">78% of observed time was active screen activity</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Engagement</div>
      <div class="line"><b>5 hints shown</b> <span class="dim">&mdash; 4 got it &middot; 1 walk-through</span></div>
      <div class="line"><b>2 quizzes attempted</b> <span class="dim">&mdash; 1/2 correct</span></div>
      <div class="line"><b>1 concept explanation</b> <span class="dim">&mdash; balancing equations</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Concepts engaged</div>
      <ul>
        <li>Distributive property with negative terms</li>
        <li>Combining like terms in linear equations</li>
        <li>Causes of the American Revolution (Stamp Act, Quartering Act)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Where Sarah got stuck</div>
      <div class="stuck-card">
        <div class="stuck-tag">Math</div>
        <div class="stuck-concept">Distributing a constant into a binomial with a negative term</div>
        <div class="stuck-context">Wrote 5x &minus; 4 instead of 5x &minus; 10 when distributing 5 into (x &minus; 2).</div>
        <div class="stuck-resolved"><span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> Resolved after a Socratic walk-through on a kinematics problem &mdash; same skill, different surface.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stuck-card">
        <div class="stuck-tag">History</div>
        <div class="stuck-concept">Identifying the second cause of the American Revolution</div>
        <div class="stuck-context">Listed &ldquo;taxation without representation&rdquo; for both blanks on a two-cause prompt.</div>
        <div class="stuck-resolved"><span class="arrow">&rarr;</span> Got it at L2 once Siko pointed at the Quartering Act and asked what colonists were forced to provide.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Strengths observed</div>
      <ul>
        <li>Recognized the need to combine like terms without prompting on problems 2 and 3</li>
        <li>Stayed engaged for the full 42-minute session across two subjects</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Recommended next session</div>
      <div class="line">Five minutes of practice on distribution with negative terms (try 6(z &minus; 3) + 4 = 22), then revisit the colonial-era timeline so the Stamp Act and Quartering Act don&rsquo;t blur together.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
      Siko refuses to give answers &mdash; every hint above is a Socratic question or nudge that asks Sarah to do the thinking.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .email-frame {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 600px;
    background: #FFFFFF;
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid rgba(20, 18, 12, 0.08);
    box-shadow:
      0 40px 80px -24px rgba(20, 18, 12, 0.22),
      0 12px 24px -10px rgba(20, 18, 12, 0.12);
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    color: #1A1A1F;
  }

  .window-chrome {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    height: 34px;
    padding: 0 14px;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #EDEDF0, #E1E1E5);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
    font-size: 12px;
    color: #5A5A66;
  }
  .lights { display: flex; gap: 6px; }
  .light {
    width: 11px; height: 11px; border-radius: 50%;
    box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 0.5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
  }
  .red    { background: #FE5F58; }
  .yellow { background: #FFBC2E; }
  .green  { background: #28C941; }
  .addr   { flex: 1; text-align: center; font-size: 11.5px; letter-spacing: 0.005em; }
  .from   { color: #8B8B96; }
  .sep    { color: #C5C5CC; margin: 0 6px; }
  .spacer { width: 49px; }

  .subject-line {
    padding: 11px 22px;
    background: #FAFAFC;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ECECF1;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #2A2A32;
  }
  .subject-eyebrow {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: #8B8B96;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-right: 8px;
  }

  .email-body {
    padding: 22px 24px 22px;
  }

  .header {
    padding-bottom: 14px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ECECF1;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8B8B96;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .title {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1A1A1F;
    margin-top: 6px;
  }
  .meta {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #6B6B78;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  .headline {
    font-size: 14.5px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: #1A1A1F;
    border-left: 3px solid #C8C8D0;
    padding-left: 12px;
    margin: 4px 0 18px;
  }

  .section { margin: 14px 0; }
  .section-eyebrow {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8B8B96;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .activity-line { font-size: 13.5px; color: #2A2A32; }
  .bar {
    background: #F3F3F5;
    border-radius: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }
  .bar-fill { background: #C8C8D0; height: 100%; }
  .bar-caption {
    font-size: 10.5px;
    color: #8B8B96;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .line {
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: #2A2A32;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 4px 0;
  }
  .line b { font-weight: 600; color: #1A1A1F; }
  .dim { color: #6B6B78; }

  ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 20px;
    color: #2A2A32;
    font-size: 13.5px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  ul li { margin: 2px 0; }

  .stuck-card {
    position: relative;
    padding: 11px 13px;
    background: #FAFAFC;
    border-left: 3px solid #FFD84D;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin: 6px 0;
  }
  .stuck-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #8B6F1F;
    background: #FFF6D9;
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 1px 6px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .stuck-concept {
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: #1A1A1F;
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }
  .stuck-context {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: #4A4A55;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .stuck-resolved {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: #6B6B78;
  }
  .arrow {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #4A4A55;
    margin-right: 4px;
  }

  .footer {
    margin-top: 18px;
    padding-top: 14px;
    border-top: 1px solid #ECECF1;
    font-size: 11.5px;
    color: #6B6B78;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
</style>
